<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-6199] camel-jms - When removing a route the jms consumer should shutdown any private thread pool the listener container may have been using</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-6199</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For example when you add / remove routes dynamically to a Camel app that starts from a JMS endpoint. Then the jms consumer may use a private thread pool for the listener container. That thread pool is enlisted in JMX.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should ensure the thread pool is shutdown and removed from JMX when the route is removed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
